It's a large, central pathway linking everything up. From the #beaches to throughout the various buildings to the #cavern-entrance, this pathway links it all up. Despite being the main pathway of transportation, thick jungle foilage covers up most of the view. The path itself is messy and is simply a dirt or sandy path, depending on where you are. During the day, the sun beats down on anyone that's here, but during the night, the forest emits a sort of eerie glow, making your hairs stand on edge. Walking along the beach and through the forest, the thing that catches your eye the most is the horizon in the distance. Even through the trees, the sun can be seen at all times. The horizon is always watching. Throughout the path, there's various types of plants and animals. Flower patches and bushes are scattered evenly throughout the jungle. Despite there being ant hills and some bird nests, no large animals can be found. There are bee hives, squirrels, and other various fauna, but no sign of any intelligent life. But you know that to be a lie.
